---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import EmailSignup from '../components/EmailSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Pairing &middot; A 12-book YA fantasy series by Caleb Arlow"
  description="Inside The Pairing: the thread system, the Threadweavers, the four-arc structure, and what is coming next. No spoilers past Book Three."
>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Inside the series">
    <Fragment slot="title">
      The world of <span class="em-italic">The Pairing.</span>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="lead">
      A magic system that maps love. A regime that decides what's allowed. A girl whose thread is the one color the regime built itself to never see.
    </Fragment>
  </PageHero>

  <!-- Threads -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-text">
      <p class="t-eyebrow">The thread system</p>
      <h2 class="t-h2" style="margin: var(--s-3) 0 var(--s-5);">Every bond shows up as a thread.</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Every citizen is paired at thirteen. The bond between two people manifests as a colored thread, and the color tells the system what kind of love it is dealing with. Gold is rare. Red is monitored. Gray means the system has interfered. White is not supposed to exist.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text">
        Threads are made from veilsilk, a substance harvested from the boundary between worlds. It is the magic in the magic system, and the people in charge are running out of it.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text">
        A small number of people can read the threads directly. Lira is one. The Threadweavers know this is dangerous. They have known for a long time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Four arcs -->
  <section class="section section-tinted">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div style="text-align: center; max-width: 56ch; margin: 0 auto var(--s-7);">
        <p class="t-eyebrow silver" style="justify-content: center;">Structure</p>
        <h2 class="t-h2" style="margin: var(--s-3) 0 var(--s-4);">Four arcs. Twelve books.</h2>
        <p class="body-text">
          The series is built in four three-book arcs. Each arc moves the story forward and asks one core question.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="arc-grid">
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc One</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Discovery <span class="arc-books">(Books 1-3)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">"What if the only person who actually sees you is the one they're going to take away?"</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            Lira meets Tieran. Their thread is a color the system has spent forty years pretending isn't real. Ages 13-14. The arc ends with a rescue, a kiss, and a choice that breaks the world wide open.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc Two</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Rebellion <span class="arc-books">(Books 4-6)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">"What does the system do when your bond becomes a banner?"</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            Two years on. Lira and Tieran are no longer kids in a cell. They're symbols, and symbols draw fire. The bond holds. The cost gets real.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc Three</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Transformation <span class="arc-books">(Books 7-9)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">"What's left of you after a war you survived together?"</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            Victory comes. So does loss. A father killed. A wedding. A baby. The arc moves from rebellion to rebuilding, and ends with the kind of love that survives losing people.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="arc-card">
          <p class="arc-num">Arc Four</p>
          <h3 class="arc-title">Legacy <span class="arc-books">(Books 10-12)</span></h3>
          <p class="arc-q">"What does the next pair do with the world the first one bled for?"</p>
          <p class="arc-blurb">
            Caleb and Nael. New bond, new gold thread, the world their parents fought for already showing cracks. The arc closes the series with the question we started with, asked again with everything earned in between.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reader on-ramp -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-text">
      <p class="t-eyebrow">Where to start</p>
      <h2 class="t-h2" style="margin: var(--s-3) 0 var(--s-5);">Read in order.</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        The Pairing is one continuous story. Start at Book One. The Discovery arc is three books and reads as one piece. All three are free with Kindle Unlimited.
      </p>

      <div class="reading-list">
        <a href="/books/thread-of-gold" class="reading-row">
          <span class="reading-num">01</span>
          <span class="reading-title">Thread of Gold</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Out now</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/books/thread-of-silver" class="reading-row">
          <span class="reading-num">02</span>
          <span class="reading-title">Thread of Silver</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Out now</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/books/thread-of-white" class="reading-row">
          <span class="reading-num">03</span>
          <span class="reading-title">Thread of White</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Out now</span>
        </a>
        <div class="reading-row reading-row-locked">
          <span class="reading-num">04</span>
          <span class="reading-title">The next book</span>
          <span class="reading-stat coming">Coming next</span>
        </div>
        <div class="reading-row reading-row-locked">
          <span class="reading-num">05-12</span>
          <span class="reading-title">The rest of the series</span>
          <span class="reading-stat">Revealed one at a time</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Email signup -->
  <section class="section section-tinted">
    <div class="wrap">
      <EmailSignup
        headline="The series drops here first."
        sub="Each new book is announced to the newsletter before anywhere else. Cover, title, release date. Then everyone else."
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .arc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--s-5);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .arc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .arc-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--thread-gold);
    padding: var(--s-6);
  }
  .arc-card:nth-child(2) { border-left-color: var(--thread-silver); }
  .arc-card:nth-child(3) { border-left-color: var(--thread-white); }
  .arc-card:nth-child(4) { border-left-color: var(--thread-gold-2); }
  .arc-num {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--thread-gold);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
  }
  .arc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--paper-50);
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
  }
  .arc-books {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .arc-q {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--paper-100);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
  }
  .arc-blurb {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
  }

  .reading-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin-top: var(--s-6);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }
  .reading-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr auto;
    gap: var(--s-4);
    align-items: center;
    padding: var(--s-4) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    transition: background var(--dur-base) var(--ease-out);
  }
  a.reading-row:hover { background: rgba(201, 168, 97, 0.04); }
  .reading-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--thread-gold);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .reading-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--paper-50);
  }
  .reading-row-locked .reading-title { color: var(--fg-muted); }
  .reading-stat {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--paper-300);
  }
  .reading-stat.coming { color: var(--thread-gold); }
</style>
